# Trivy misconfiguration suppressions for infra/.
#
# Each entry below is a deliberate, documented decision for THIS context: a
# public static-site portfolio (S3 + CloudFront) with no auth, forms, logins,
# or sensitive data. Suppressing them keeps the gate green on accepted trade-
# offs while STILL failing CI on any new misconfiguration not listed here.
# Triaged 2026-06-11; full cost rationale in the PR that introduced this gate.

# HIGH: CloudFront distribution does not use a WAF.
# A brochure site has nothing to protect behind a WAF (no auth, forms, or user
# data). AWS WAF would add ~$10-15/mo across the prod + preview distributions
# for no meaningful risk reduction. Accepted.
AVD-AWS-0011

# HIGH: S3 bucket not encrypted with a customer-managed KMS key.
# The buckets serve PUBLIC website assets; default SSE-S3 (AES256) is already
# on. A customer-managed KMS key adds key-management cost and request fees for
# zero confidentiality benefit on content that is, by design, public. Accepted.
AVD-AWS-0132

# MEDIUM: S3 bucket versioning not enabled.
# Bucket contents are build artifacts, fully redeployable from git + CI. Git is
# the source of truth, not the bucket, so versioning adds storage cost without
# protecting anything irreplaceable. Accepted.
AVD-AWS-0090

# MEDIUM: CloudFront access logging not enabled.
# Adds a logging bucket and storage cost; a personal portfolio has no audit or
# analytics requirement that justifies it. Accepted.
AVD-AWS-0010

# LOW: S3 bucket server access logging not enabled.
# Same rationale as CloudFront logging: public static assets, low audit value,
# avoids an extra log bucket. Accepted.
AVD-AWS-0089
